Anatomy of an HTML Element

<p>HTML is a markup language</p> 
Entirely its an element

<p> - Opening tag (Name of the element)  i.e p (in this case) wrapped in <p and >

HTML is a markup language - Content (text in this case) but it might be another element (child element) Some elements have no content (<img>)

</p> - Closing tag (/Name of the element)  i.e p (in this case) wrapped in </p and >

Text

<h1> > Primary Heading
<h2> > Secondary Heading

Things to remember:
There is only one primary heading
